ome.smuggler.core.msg

Interface ChannelSource<T>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    MessageSource<M,D>, SchedulingSource<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CountedScheduleTask, EnqueueTask, ScheduleTask, SourceQueue

    public interface ChannelSource<T>
    Encapsulates the sending of an asynchronous message along a channel.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void send(T data)
      Inputs data into the channel and returns immediately.
      default void uncheckedSend(T data)
      Same as send but masks any exception as a runtime (unchecked) exception and throws it as such without any wrapping.

    • Method Detail

      • send

        void send(T data)
   throws java.lang.Exception
        Inputs data into the channel and returns immediately. This is an asynchronous operation, so that the sender never waits for the receiver to get the data.
        Parameters:
        data - the message to send.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the input is null.
        java.lang.Exception - if the data could not be input into the channel.

      • uncheckedSend

        default void uncheckedSend(T data)
        Same as send but masks any exception as a runtime (unchecked) exception and throws it as such without any wrapping.
